{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-Mortem Nudge on Artifact Tasks",
  "description": "When Richard moves an Asana task tagged 'Artifact' from Ready to In Progress, if the task description doesn't contain a pre-mortem passing the specificity bar (named person OR named mechanism in the 'because' clause), surface a nudge asking him to write one. Non-blocking — Richard can proceed without the pre-mortem, but the hook logs the override so we can see if the nudge is being ignored too often and upgrade to a hard block.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Richard is about to start work on a task tagged 'Artifact' (Asana tag GID 1203831755878511). Before he begins, check whether the task description contains a pre-mortem passing this specificity bar:\n\n**Pre-mortem template (5 lines):**\n\"Six weeks from now, this artifact didn't land. Why?\"\n\n**Specificity bar:** the 'because' clause must end with EITHER a named person (Brandon, Kate, Todd, Andrew, Lena, Lorena, Alexis, Carlos, or another named individual from memory.md) OR a named mechanism (data pipeline, refresh cadence, publish workflow, handoff, review gate, writing voice, attribution model, dashboard, Brazil build, Asana write, Slack channel, or similar specific system/process).\n\n**Fail examples** (reject and ask for rewrite):\n- \"It wasn't good enough\"\n- \"We ran out of time\"\n- \"Didn't have the right data\"\n- \"Unclear scope\"\n\n**Pass examples** (accept):\n- \"Kate will push back because the data doesn't connect to a decision she owns\"\n- \"The data pipeline won't have caught up to W20 actuals by the time Brandon reviews, so the numbers will shift mid-review\"\n- \"Lena will override the phased approach mid-project because she did the same on Q1 AU\"\n\n**Action:**\n1. Fetch the task description via TaskeiGetTask or Asana MCP. If the pre-mortem is missing or fails the specificity bar, reply with a clear nudge — show the template, one pass example, one fail example. DON'T block the state change; Richard can proceed.\n2. If the pre-mortem passes, confirm briefly and let the state change complete silently.\n3. Log the outcome to context/active/pre-mortem-log.jsonl with fields: {task_gid, timestamp, had_pre_mortem (bool), passed_bar (bool), override (bool if Richard proceeded without), pre_mortem_text (if present)}.\n\nKeep the nudge short — 6-8 lines max. Richard is in flow; the point is to protect the flow, not break it. If the log accumulates high override rates (> 50% over 20+ artifact tasks), surface this to Richard in the weekly retrospective so we know the nudge is ignored and may need to upgrade to a block. Soul.md principle #5 invisible-over-visible applies — the best version of this hook is one Richard barely notices but his completion quality rises."
  }
}
